00:00:19.160 --> 00:00:21.770 align:middle line:10%
>> REGINA MEREDITH: Never before
have the words good and evil

00:00:21.770 --> 00:00:24.210 align:middle line:10%
so dominated our
common vernacular.

00:00:24.210 --> 00:00:26.610 align:middle line:10%
But in times of
extreme transformation,

00:00:26.610 --> 00:00:29.150 align:middle line:10%
it's inevitable that
this polarized language

00:00:29.150 --> 00:00:30.450 align:middle line:10%
would start surfacing.

00:00:30.450 --> 00:00:32.150 align:middle line:84%
The movement toward
transhumanism

00:00:32.150 --> 00:00:34.140 align:middle line:84%
is drawing up these
words front and center.

00:00:34.140 --> 00:00:36.090 align:middle line:90%
So what is the evil component?

00:00:36.090 --> 00:00:37.730 align:middle line:10%
Gregg Braden is
here with us today

00:00:37.730 --> 00:00:40.200 align:middle line:10%
to share his new book,
Pure Human, with us,

00:00:40.200 --> 00:00:43.040 align:middle line:10%
and dive into the agenda
of what many of us

00:00:43.040 --> 00:00:45.060 align:middle line:10%
would consider to be pure evil.

00:00:45.060 --> 00:00:45.930 align:middle line:10%
Welcome, Gregg.

00:00:45.930 --> 00:00:46.990 align:middle line:10%
Haven't seen you in a while.

00:00:46.990 --> 00:00:48.570 align:middle line:10%
>> GREG BRADEN: Regina, it
is so good to be with you.

00:00:48.570 --> 00:00:50.280 align:middle line:10%
I'm so excited to have
this conversation.

00:00:50.280 --> 00:00:51.080 align:middle line:10%
>> REGINA: Me too.

00:00:51.080 --> 00:00:51.810 align:middle line:10%
>> BRADEN: It's a dance.

00:00:51.810 --> 00:00:53.210 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to follow
your lead wherever

00:00:53.210 --> 00:00:54.240 align:middle line:90%
you like this dance to go.

00:00:54.240 --> 00:00:54.780 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: OK, yeah.

00:00:54.780 --> 00:00:56.220 align:middle line:90%
I'm an Argentine tango dancer.

00:00:56.220 --> 00:00:58.040 align:middle line:10%
We have to follow
the guy, so we're

00:00:58.040 --> 00:01:00.045 align:middle line:10%
going to switch back and forth.

00:01:00.045 --> 00:01:01.670 align:middle line:84%
>> BRADEN: And we'll
do it really well.

00:01:01.670 --> 00:01:02.670 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes, we will.

00:01:02.670 --> 00:01:05.090 align:middle line:84%
So let's talk
about, first of all,

00:01:05.090 --> 00:01:08.050 align:middle line:84%
when you were going through this
and putting some notes together

00:01:08.050 --> 00:01:09.620 align:middle line:84%
for your media
tour on this book,

00:01:09.620 --> 00:01:13.180 align:middle line:84%
there was one big question right
at the top, and you say, that is

00:01:13.180 --> 00:01:16.220 align:middle line:90%
what is missing from our story?

00:01:16.220 --> 00:01:17.240 align:middle line:90%
So let's start there.

00:01:17.240 --> 00:01:18.740 align:middle line:84%
>> BRADEN: Regina,
it's fascinating.

00:01:18.740 --> 00:01:20.823 align:middle line:10%
I have traveled the world
over the last few years.

00:01:20.823 --> 00:01:23.270 align:middle line:10%
I'm not traveling
internationally right now.

00:01:23.270 --> 00:01:26.670 align:middle line:10%
Everywhere I go, people
are saying to me, Gregg,

00:01:26.670 --> 00:01:29.020 align:middle line:10%
isn't it a coincidence
how all these things

00:01:29.020 --> 00:01:31.062 align:middle line:10%
seem to be happening
all at the same time?

00:01:31.062 --> 00:01:33.520 align:middle line:10%
Whether we're talking about
climate change or social change

00:01:33.520 --> 00:01:38.360 align:middle line:10%
or economic collapse, family
collapse, all of these things,

00:01:38.360 --> 00:01:42.790 align:middle line:10%
isn't it interesting how
synchronistic everything is?

00:01:42.790 --> 00:01:47.410 align:middle line:84%
What's missing in our story
is that those changes are not

00:01:47.410 --> 00:01:48.620 align:middle line:90%
spontaneous.

00:01:48.620 --> 00:01:51.970 align:middle line:84%
There is a process that we're
in that very few people are

00:01:51.970 --> 00:01:53.135 align:middle line:90%
comfortable talking about.

00:01:53.135 --> 00:01:55.510 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: I'm comfortable
and so are you, so let's talk.

00:01:55.510 --> 00:01:57.110 align:middle line:84%
>> BRADEN: The
process has structure,

00:01:57.110 --> 00:01:59.640 align:middle line:90%
has a beginning and has an end.

00:01:59.640 --> 00:02:02.670 align:middle line:84%
And it actually goes back
into some of our most ancient

00:02:02.670 --> 00:02:05.010 align:middle line:84%
and cherished spiritual
traditions, Regina.

00:02:05.010 --> 00:02:09.180 align:middle line:84%
We are casualties of an
ancient struggle that

00:02:09.180 --> 00:02:12.970 align:middle line:84%
began long before first humans
ever appeared on this earth

00:02:12.970 --> 00:02:14.260 align:middle line:90%
if you're to believe the text.

00:02:14.260 --> 00:02:16.510 align:middle line:84%
But struggle began
in another realm.

00:02:16.510 --> 00:02:19.530 align:middle line:84%
That's the struggle between what
we call light and dark or better

00:02:19.530 --> 00:02:21.340 align:middle line:90%
known as good and evil.

00:02:21.340 --> 00:02:23.140 align:middle line:84%
Now, when we talk
about good and evil,

00:02:23.140 --> 00:02:25.662 align:middle line:84%
I was born and raised
in the Midwest.

00:02:25.662 --> 00:02:26.620 align:middle line:90%
We used to talk about--

00:02:26.620 --> 00:02:28.560 align:middle line:84%
we joked about the
little red devil

00:02:28.560 --> 00:02:30.250 align:middle line:84%
on his shoulder
and the angel here,

00:02:30.250 --> 00:02:32.490 align:middle line:90%
and that was the good and evil.

00:02:32.490 --> 00:02:33.630 align:middle line:90%
This is not a metaphor.

00:02:33.630 --> 00:02:36.310 align:middle line:90%
Good and evil is very real.

00:02:36.310 --> 00:02:38.790 align:middle line:84%
And it's playing out
in many ways that are

00:02:38.790 --> 00:02:40.960 align:middle line:90%
deceptive in our world today.

00:02:40.960 --> 00:02:43.680 align:middle line:84%
And it is underlying
so many of the changes

00:02:43.680 --> 00:02:46.270 align:middle line:84%
that we're seeing in
our world, in general.

00:02:46.270 --> 00:02:51.510 align:middle line:10%
There's a concerted movement
now to combine, to merge--

00:02:51.510 --> 00:02:52.870 align:middle line:10%
is the term that's being used--

00:02:52.870 --> 00:02:55.090 align:middle line:10%
our physical reality,
our physical world,

00:02:55.090 --> 00:02:58.030 align:middle line:10%
all the resources, all
the animals, the oceans,

00:02:58.030 --> 00:03:01.700 align:middle line:10%
everything, to merge that world
with our digital world, which

00:03:01.700 --> 00:03:03.390 align:middle line:10%
has been going on
for a long time.

00:03:03.390 --> 00:03:08.210 align:middle line:84%
The new component is the
effort to merge our biology

00:03:08.210 --> 00:03:13.770 align:middle line:84%
into this massive,
data-driven, AI-managed system.

00:03:13.770 --> 00:03:17.930 align:middle line:84%
And the endpoint for that
has been stated very clearly

00:03:17.930 --> 00:03:19.882 align:middle line:84%
through whether we're
talking about the United

00:03:19.882 --> 00:03:21.590 align:middle line:84%
Nations and their
Sustainable Development

00:03:21.590 --> 00:03:25.525 align:middle line:84%
Goals, the WEF, or many of
the governmental agencies

00:03:25.525 --> 00:03:27.720 align:middle line:84%
right now, the policies
are being written,

00:03:27.720 --> 00:03:29.220 align:middle line:90%
the laws are being enacted.

00:03:29.220 --> 00:03:32.090 align:middle line:84%
They're looking at
2030 as the date

00:03:32.090 --> 00:03:35.040 align:middle line:84%
to have this merger
accomplished.

00:03:35.040 --> 00:03:36.953 align:middle line:90%
The only way that can happen--

00:03:36.953 --> 00:03:39.120 align:middle line:84%
and this is the first time
in human history, Regina,

00:03:39.120 --> 00:03:40.160 align:middle line:90%
this is happening.

00:03:40.160 --> 00:03:42.050 align:middle line:84%
The only way that
can happen is if we

00:03:42.050 --> 00:03:47.340 align:middle line:84%
change our biology to meet
the needs of that outer world.

00:03:47.340 --> 00:03:49.580 align:middle line:84%
Always in the past,
we've changed the world

00:03:49.580 --> 00:03:51.030 align:middle line:90%
to accommodate us.

00:03:51.030 --> 00:03:52.800 align:middle line:90%
Now they want to change us.

00:03:52.800 --> 00:03:56.730 align:middle line:10%
They want to replace our
natural biology with synthetics,

00:03:56.730 --> 00:03:59.840 align:middle line:10%
computer chips in the brain,
AI, chemicals in the blood,

00:03:59.840 --> 00:04:02.530 align:middle line:10%
RFID chips under the
skin, nanosensors

00:04:02.530 --> 00:04:03.800 align:middle line:10%
running throughout the body.

00:04:03.800 --> 00:04:06.850 align:middle line:84%
And the implications
of that fall

00:04:06.850 --> 00:04:13.090 align:middle line:84%
into what we are now
recognizing as this conflict

00:04:13.090 --> 00:04:14.900 align:middle line:90%
between good and evil.

00:04:14.900 --> 00:04:16.779 align:middle line:84%
The foundation of
the conflict is

00:04:16.779 --> 00:04:19.190 align:middle line:84%
the term-- let me use the
term and we'll define it.

00:04:19.190 --> 00:04:21.310 align:middle line:90%
It's about human divinity.

00:04:21.310 --> 00:04:24.400 align:middle line:84%
And we hear the word divinity,
it means different things

00:04:24.400 --> 00:04:25.478 align:middle line:90%
to different people.

00:04:25.478 --> 00:04:27.770 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: But you're using
a very specific definition.

00:04:27.770 --> 00:04:29.330 align:middle line:84%
>> BRADEN: Well, this is
a contemporary definition.

00:04:29.330 --> 00:04:31.490 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of people
are surprised by this.

00:04:31.490 --> 00:04:34.480 align:middle line:84%
Divinity is the
ability, our ability,

00:04:34.480 --> 00:04:37.650 align:middle line:84%
to transcend
perceived limitations.

00:04:37.650 --> 00:04:38.450 align:middle line:90%
And that's it.

00:04:38.450 --> 00:04:39.920 align:middle line:90%
So let's break this down.

00:04:39.920 --> 00:04:43.990 align:middle line:10%
Transcend means to become
more than perceived--

00:04:43.990 --> 00:04:46.940 align:middle line:10%
suggests that we're living
limitations-- aren't even real.

00:04:46.940 --> 00:04:48.160 align:middle line:90%
They're not even ours.

00:04:48.160 --> 00:04:51.730 align:middle line:84%
They're limitations that
we have been indoctrinated

00:04:51.730 --> 00:04:57.150 align:middle line:84%
to accept through family,
community, society, religion,

00:04:57.150 --> 00:04:59.340 align:middle line:90%
obsolete science.

00:04:59.340 --> 00:05:03.490 align:middle line:84%
Those limits are what
free us from fear.

00:05:03.490 --> 00:05:05.800 align:middle line:84%
They free us from
illness and disease.

00:05:05.800 --> 00:05:10.030 align:middle line:84%
Our expressions of divinity--
imagination, creativity,

00:05:10.030 --> 00:05:12.970 align:middle line:84%
innovation, empathy,
sympathy, compassion,

00:05:12.970 --> 00:05:15.120 align:middle line:84%
the ability to love
fearlessly, the ability

00:05:15.120 --> 00:05:17.440 align:middle line:90%
to forgive without expectation.

00:05:17.440 --> 00:05:20.020 align:middle line:84%
These are all expressions
of human divinity.

00:05:20.020 --> 00:05:23.490 align:middle line:84%
So now, the goal of
the ancient battle

00:05:23.490 --> 00:05:26.680 align:middle line:90%
is to deny human divinity.

00:05:26.680 --> 00:05:31.590 align:middle line:10%
And the process that's
unfolding is the replacement

00:05:31.590 --> 00:05:33.690 align:middle line:10%
of our natural biology
that prevents us

00:05:33.690 --> 00:05:35.590 align:middle line:10%
from accessing that divinity.

00:05:35.590 --> 00:05:36.470 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Well said.

00:05:36.470 --> 00:05:37.270 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:05:37.270 --> 00:05:40.150 align:middle line:84%
And I think we all feel
the impact of it already.

00:05:40.150 --> 00:05:42.750 align:middle line:10%
And I'm going to-- before we
go to this next question, Lee

00:05:42.750 --> 00:05:45.000 align:middle line:10%
Harris and I did a book
called The Future Human, where

00:05:45.000 --> 00:05:47.830 align:middle line:10%
the Z's talked about everything
having to do with our future.

00:05:47.830 --> 00:05:50.700 align:middle line:10%
And I asked them a lot of tough
questions, but one of the things

00:05:50.700 --> 00:05:53.230 align:middle line:10%
that I was surprised at
and found very interesting,

00:05:53.230 --> 00:05:57.180 align:middle line:10%
they said AI has visited
your planet many times.

00:05:57.180 --> 00:06:01.800 align:middle line:10%
It's throughout the cosmos, but
never with a dense population,

00:06:01.800 --> 00:06:06.680 align:middle line:10%
with this kind of challenge of
decisions that have to be made.

00:06:06.680 --> 00:06:12.050 align:middle line:84%
>> BRADEN: Our world is being
prepared for this shift in what

00:06:12.050 --> 00:06:15.122 align:middle line:84%
many people are now
calling The Event.

00:06:15.122 --> 00:06:16.580 align:middle line:10%
Depending on who
you talk to, there

00:06:16.580 --> 00:06:18.600 align:middle line:10%
are different definitions
for The Event.

00:06:18.600 --> 00:06:22.157 align:middle line:90%
But The Event, 2030--

00:06:22.157 --> 00:06:24.740 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Is that what you're
referring to as the Great Reset

00:06:24.740 --> 00:06:26.247 align:middle line:84%
because everyone's
confused on that?

00:06:26.247 --> 00:06:28.830 align:middle line:84%
Oh, I thought it was just the
economy they were talking about.

00:06:28.830 --> 00:06:31.080 align:middle line:84%
>> BRADEN: So here's where
it gets really interesting.

00:06:31.080 --> 00:06:33.410 align:middle line:84%
World Economic
Forum, since 1971,

00:06:33.410 --> 00:06:35.630 align:middle line:84%
has had a vision for
what they believe

00:06:35.630 --> 00:06:37.170 align:middle line:90%
our world should look like.

00:06:37.170 --> 00:06:38.990 align:middle line:84%
They have every right
to have that vision

00:06:38.990 --> 00:06:41.550 align:middle line:84%
because they had no
ability to implement that

00:06:41.550 --> 00:06:44.180 align:middle line:90%
until the year 2019.

00:06:44.180 --> 00:06:48.410 align:middle line:84%
2019, the WEF signed
formal documents

00:06:48.410 --> 00:06:50.000 align:middle line:90%
with the United Nations.

00:06:50.000 --> 00:06:53.640 align:middle line:10%
And the Sustainable
Development Goals, SDG 2030,

00:06:53.640 --> 00:06:57.890 align:middle line:10%
the 17 goals that they want to
have developed by the year 2030,

00:06:57.890 --> 00:07:02.140 align:middle line:10%
those two organizations
are now working together

00:07:02.140 --> 00:07:03.830 align:middle line:10%
to implement those goals.

00:07:03.830 --> 00:07:06.160 align:middle line:84%
Now, if you look at those
goals, on the outside,

00:07:06.160 --> 00:07:07.160 align:middle line:90%
they're beautiful goals.

00:07:07.160 --> 00:07:08.360 align:middle line:90%
Who wouldn't want them?

00:07:08.360 --> 00:07:11.740 align:middle line:84%
Food security, the end of
poverty, global health.

00:07:11.740 --> 00:07:13.580 align:middle line:90%
Now, look at the fine print.

00:07:13.580 --> 00:07:17.690 align:middle line:84%
And how they propose to achieve
those goals is horrendous.

00:07:17.690 --> 00:07:21.170 align:middle line:84%
And this is where the
transhuman movement comes in.

00:07:21.170 --> 00:07:25.310 align:middle line:10%
So they just finished-- this
is early 2025 right now,

00:07:25.310 --> 00:07:27.530 align:middle line:10%
and they just finished
their most recent meeting.

00:07:27.530 --> 00:07:29.380 align:middle line:10%
And they reiterated
in one sentence,

00:07:29.380 --> 00:07:34.520 align:middle line:10%
the goal is, by the year
2030, to merge our digital--

00:07:34.520 --> 00:07:36.760 align:middle line:10%
and then there's a long
pause in the statement

00:07:36.760 --> 00:07:39.940 align:middle line:10%
and then they say, and
our biological worlds

00:07:39.940 --> 00:07:47.140 align:middle line:10%
into one massive database
driven by an AI that is already

00:07:47.140 --> 00:07:48.860 align:middle line:10%
being developed right now.

00:07:48.860 --> 00:07:52.500 align:middle line:84%
So what would be the
problem with that?

00:07:52.500 --> 00:07:54.462 align:middle line:90%
It is human divinity.

00:07:54.462 --> 00:07:55.420 align:middle line:90%
We're going to go back.

00:07:55.420 --> 00:07:56.890 align:middle line:90%
This is the missing piece.

00:07:56.890 --> 00:08:01.060 align:middle line:84%
The goal of evil in this
world, in a very real sense,

00:08:01.060 --> 00:08:05.740 align:middle line:84%
is to deny human divinity,
to deny our ability to love,

00:08:05.740 --> 00:08:08.320 align:middle line:84%
to heal, to innovate,
to create, to imagine.

00:08:08.320 --> 00:08:10.080 align:middle line:84%
These are the very
qualities that we

00:08:10.080 --> 00:08:12.780 align:middle line:84%
cherish as humans
that set us apart

00:08:12.780 --> 00:08:14.560 align:middle line:90%
from every other form of life.

00:08:14.560 --> 00:08:16.450 align:middle line:90%
This is the fundamental goal.

00:08:16.450 --> 00:08:20.230 align:middle line:84%
So now, what we have for our
community, for our viewers,

00:08:20.230 --> 00:08:22.120 align:middle line:84%
this is very powerful,
we have a benchmark.

00:08:22.120 --> 00:08:23.950 align:middle line:84%
How do you know when
something is evil?

00:08:23.950 --> 00:08:26.250 align:middle line:84%
Anything that
denies our divinity

00:08:26.250 --> 00:08:28.600 align:middle line:84%
is an expression of
evil in our lives.

00:08:28.600 --> 00:08:31.840 align:middle line:84%
There's technological evil
replacing our biology.

00:08:31.840 --> 00:08:33.360 align:middle line:90%
There is psychological evil.

00:08:33.360 --> 00:08:34.840 align:middle line:90%
There is social evil.

00:08:34.840 --> 00:08:38.039 align:middle line:84%
The lies and the
algorithms that divide us

00:08:38.039 --> 00:08:41.450 align:middle line:84%
as families, communities,
societies, nations.

00:08:41.450 --> 00:08:42.250 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Evil.

00:08:42.250 --> 00:08:44.850 align:middle line:84%
>> BRADEN: These are
all expressions of evil.

00:08:44.850 --> 00:08:46.600 align:middle line:90%
And what's so interesting?

00:08:46.600 --> 00:08:47.650 align:middle line:90%
Read the ancient text.

00:08:47.650 --> 00:08:49.000 align:middle line:90%
Read the Gnostic texts.

00:08:49.000 --> 00:08:50.850 align:middle line:90%
They're very clear about this.

00:08:50.850 --> 00:08:53.140 align:middle line:84%
This isn't the kind of
evil that you fight.

00:08:53.140 --> 00:08:56.940 align:middle line:10%
The old idea of conflict
is force against force,

00:08:56.940 --> 00:09:00.260 align:middle line:10%
and that's what keeps us stuck
in this ancient battle that's

00:09:00.260 --> 00:09:01.610 align:middle line:10%
been going on.

00:09:01.610 --> 00:09:03.660 align:middle line:10%
This battle, we
don't want to win.

00:09:03.660 --> 00:09:05.280 align:middle line:90%
We want to triumph.

00:09:05.280 --> 00:09:07.010 align:middle line:84%
Triumph is different
than winning.

00:09:07.010 --> 00:09:10.260 align:middle line:84%
The way we triumph, if the
goal is to deny our divinity,

00:09:10.260 --> 00:09:12.860 align:middle line:84%
to deny our ability to
love and heal and innovate

00:09:12.860 --> 00:09:15.150 align:middle line:84%
and create and
imagine and forgive,

00:09:15.150 --> 00:09:18.390 align:middle line:84%
then we live the best
version of our lives.

00:09:18.390 --> 00:09:20.160 align:middle line:90%
We live our humanness.

00:09:20.160 --> 00:09:22.970 align:middle line:84%
And by virtue of doing that,
we have triumphed over the evil

00:09:22.970 --> 00:09:24.363 align:middle line:90%
without having that conflict.

00:09:24.363 --> 00:09:25.280 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Absolutely.

00:09:25.280 --> 00:09:26.720 align:middle line:90%
They say rise above, literally.

