else ready for them.

00:36:58.630 --> 00:36:59.710 align:middle line:90%
Where do you begin?

00:36:59.710 --> 00:37:01.543 align:middle line:84%
>> BRADEN: I think it
goes deeper than that.

00:37:01.543 --> 00:37:04.320 align:middle line:84%
I think we owe it to
the younger generation

00:37:04.320 --> 00:37:08.520 align:middle line:84%
to instill within them a
sense of pride and value

00:37:08.520 --> 00:37:10.680 align:middle line:84%
for their humanness,
for who they are,

00:37:10.680 --> 00:37:14.890 align:middle line:84%
that there's something inside
of them that is so rare,

00:37:14.890 --> 00:37:16.980 align:middle line:84%
and it is ancient,
and it is precious,

00:37:16.980 --> 00:37:20.140 align:middle line:84%
and it is beautiful that
is worth preserving.

00:37:20.140 --> 00:37:22.140 align:middle line:84%
Because nobody's telling
our young kids that.

00:37:22.140 --> 00:37:23.620 align:middle line:84%
They're telling them
that they're flawed.

00:37:23.620 --> 00:37:25.270 align:middle line:84%
They need something
outside of their body.

00:37:25.270 --> 00:37:27.687 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: That their mere
presence is killing the planet.

00:37:27.687 --> 00:37:30.225 align:middle line:84%
>> BRADEN: All right, so
by virtue of being carbon,

00:37:30.225 --> 00:37:32.100 align:middle line:84%
that carbon-based life
is killing the planet.

00:37:32.100 --> 00:37:32.790 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Killing the planet.

00:37:32.790 --> 00:37:33.590 align:middle line:90%
That's not true.

00:37:33.590 --> 00:37:37.760 align:middle line:84%
>> BRADEN: When we begin to
instill these values within

00:37:37.760 --> 00:37:42.680 align:middle line:84%
