with that is the appreciation

00:37:42.680 --> 00:37:45.930 align:middle line:84%
for our own imagination,
our own creativity.

00:37:45.930 --> 00:37:48.950 align:middle line:84%
And we feel less of
an urgency to use

00:37:48.950 --> 00:37:52.310 align:middle line:90%
ChatGPT and things like that.

00:37:52.310 --> 00:37:54.990 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Because we are
unique in and of ourselves.

00:37:54.990 --> 00:37:56.750 align:middle line:84%
>> BRADEN: That's
where I would begin.

00:37:56.750 --> 00:37:59.260 align:middle line:84%
Parents, right now, I know
it's a very different way

00:37:59.260 --> 00:38:00.060 align:middle line:90%
of thinking.

00:38:00.060 --> 00:38:03.290 align:middle line:84%
I think, obviously,
we all know to limit

00:38:03.290 --> 00:38:07.970 align:middle line:84%
the use of how these things and
to regulate how these things are

00:38:07.970 --> 00:38:08.970 align:middle line:90%
being used in our lives.

00:38:08.970 --> 00:38:14.580 align:middle line:84%
But if we go to the core of the
problem, then it solves itself.

00:38:14.580 --> 00:38:22.010 align:middle line:10%
When young people develop that
sense of appreciation, of pride

00:38:22.010 --> 00:38:24.680 align:middle line:10%
for what it means
to be a human life

00:38:24.680 --> 00:38:26.750 align:middle line:10%
and the extraordinary
potentials,

00:38:26.750 --> 00:38:31.030 align:middle line:10%
that they see on those movies,
they have within themselves,

00:38:31.030 --> 00:38:35.180 align:middle line:10%
then they are focused
on developing those.

00:38:35.180 --> 00:38:37.960 align:middle line:84%
They don't feel the need to
have something do it for them,

00:38:37.960 --> 00:38:41.740 align:middle line:84%
because they know the most
precious thing, Regina, is it

00:38:41.740 --> 00:38:43.540 align:middle line:90%
all comes down to love.

00:38:43.540 --> 00:38:46.210 align:middle line:84%
And what we're asking
ourselves, as a society,

00:38:46.210 --> 00:38:47.930 align:middle line:84%
and what we're asking
our young people,

00:38:47.930 --> 00:38:52.210 align:middle line:84%
do we love ourselves enough to
accept the deep truth of what

00:38:52.210 --> 00:38:54.430 align:middle line:84%
it means to be human
and the responsibility

00:38:54.430 --> 00:38:56.030 align:middle line:90%
of human divinity?

00:38:56.030 --> 00:38:58.700 align:middle line:84%
Do we love ourselves
enough to accept it?

00:38:58.700 --> 00:39:01.220 align:middle line:90%
And the answer is not verbal.

00:39:01.220 --> 00:39:03.748 align:middle line:84%
It's the way we live our
lives, the choices that we

00:39:03.748 --> 00:39:03.820 align:middle line:90%
make with our lives.

00:39:03.820 --> 00:39:04.760 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: I agree with that.

00:39:04.760 --> 00:39:06.430 align:middle line:84%
>> BRADEN: And that's what I
